[["1823237-111","black-walnut","Old Dominion Hall, Williamsburg, VA 23186, USA","Black walnut","Juglans nigra",37.271622,-76.71252,"Mature black walnut tree. Many nuts on the ground as of late October 2022. Access: Public.","community","https://fallingfruit.org/locations/1823237","2022-10-26 03:13:39 UTC","Public","open",true,"Falling Fruit access: Public."],["1823236-111","black-walnut","201 James Blair Dr, Williamsburg, VA 23185, USA","Black walnut","Juglans nigra",37.271921,-76.712184,"Large black walnut tree. Many nuts visible as of late October 2022. Access: Public.","community","https://fallingfruit.org/locations/1823236","2022-10-26 03:13:11 UTC","Public","open",true,"Falling Fruit access: Public."],["1809486-111","black-walnut","202 N England St, Williamsburg, VA 23185, USA","Black walnut","Juglans nigra",37.272679,-76.700215,"Access: Public.","community","https://fallingfruit.org/locations/1809486","2022-04-23 05:00:16 UTC","Public","open",true,"Falling Fruit access: Public."],["2282831-111","black-walnut","227 Richmond Rd, Williamsburg, VA 23185, USA","Black walnut","Juglans nigra",37.27269342276618,-76.7107028581955,"Between the sidewalk and street in front of the Presbyterian church. Very mature tree, plenty of green husks on the ground and branches as of mid-October 2025 Access: Public.","community","https://fallingfruit.org/locations/2282831","2025-10-11 21:51:57 UTC","Public","open",true,"Falling Fruit access: Public."],["2282832-111","black-walnut","227 Richmond Rd, Williamsburg, VA 23185, USA","Black walnut","Juglans nigra",37.27269342276618,-76.7107028581955,"Between the sidewalk and street in front of the Presbyterian church. Very mature tree, plenty of green husks on the ground and branches as of mid-October 2025 Access: Public.","community","https://fallingfruit.org/locations/2282832","2025-10-11 21:51:57 UTC","Public","open",true,"Falling Fruit access: Public."],["1809487-111","black-walnut","110 Scotland St, Williamsburg, VA 23185, USA","Black walnut","Juglans nigra",37.274343,-76.701281,"Access: Public.","community","https://fallingfruit.org/locations/1809487","2022-04-23 05:00:18 UTC","Public","open",true,"Falling Fruit access: Public."],["1823235-93","hickory","Old Dominion Hall, Williamsburg, VA 23186, USA","Pecan","Carya illinoinensis",37.272581,-76.71195,"Four mature pecan trees. Last time I visited, they seemed to be dropping nuts with the green hulls still on and few visibly ripe nuts without hulls, but the trees appear otherwise healthy. Access: Public.","community","https://fallingfruit.org/locations/1823235","2022-10-26 02:37:47 UTC","Public","open",true,"Falling Fruit access: Public."],["1823234-93","hickory","354-370 Richmond Rd, Williamsburg, VA 23186, USA","Pecan","Carya illinoinensis",37.273015,-76.712877,"Several mature pecan trees. Access: Public.","community","https://fallingfruit.org/locations/1823234","2022-10-26 02:32:16 UTC","Public","open",true,"Falling Fruit access: Public."],["1905248-93","hickory","427 Scotland St, Williamsburg, VA 23185, USA","Pecan","Carya illinoinensis",37.273772,-76.707148,"Pecan overhanging the side of what is currently housing the Global Research Institute (owned by William & Mary). Nuts don't look like they're falling ripe, though. Access: Private but overhanging.","community","https://fallingfruit.org/locations/1905248","2023-09-22 00:45:08 UTC","Private but overhanging","private",false,"Falling Fruit access: Private but overhanging."],["1072502-358","ink-autumn-olive","Autumn-olive","Autumn-olive","Elaeagnus umbellata",37.26947634454665,-76.71068225023191,"Access: Public. Falling Fruit season: August-November.","community","https://fallingfruit.org/locations/1072502","2016-02-26 19:08:11 UTC","Public","open",true,"Falling Fruit access: Public."],["1827858-358","ink-autumn-olive","305 N Boundary St, Williamsburg, VA 23185, USA","Autumn-olive","Elaeagnus umbellata",37.274132,-76.707606,"Smaller autumn olive plants. They're unfortunately invasive but might as well eat the berries. The plants are small enough that I'm not sure how much fruit they'll produce. Not sure about the season, but another plant nearby fruits in early October, so that ma","community","https://fallingfruit.org/locations/1827858","2023-05-27 02:34:51 UTC","Private but overhanging","private",false,"Falling Fruit access: Private but overhanging."],["1072501-116","pawpaw","720 Jamestown Rd, Williamsburg, VA 23185, USA","Pawpaw","Asimina triloba",37.265647,-76.718801,"Shanandoah pawpaw Access: Public. Falling Fruit season: August-September.","community","https://fallingfruit.org/locations/1072501","2023-09-22 00:04:58 UTC","Public","open",true,"Falling Fruit access: Public."],["1072503-116","pawpaw","Giles Hall, 500 B Ukrop Way, Williamsburg, VA 23185, USA","Pawpaw","Asimina triloba",37.269652,-76.718235,"A number of trees on both sides of the bridge. The side of the marker had a few fruits, but the height of the trees means this will likely be a low-reward area and the fruit should probably be left for critters. Falling Fruit season: August-September.","community","https://fallingfruit.org/locations/1072503","2023-05-27 02:28:26 UTC","","unknown",false,"Access unknown in Falling Fruit."],["1823672-116","pawpaw","Landrum Hall, 601 Landrum Dr, Williamsburg, VA 23185, USA","Pawpaw","Asimina triloba",37.270398,-76.713235,"Clump of pawpaw trees across from Landrum hall. As of May 2023, there are a few fruiting trees. Relatively easy access, as the trees are right on the edge of a path. Access: Public. Falling Fruit season: August-September.","community","https://fallingfruit.org/locations/1823672","2023-05-27 02:31:00 UTC","Public","open",true,"Falling Fruit access: Public."],["1827863-116","pawpaw","N Henry St at Highland Park, Williamsburg, VA 23185, USA","Pawpaw","Asimina triloba",37.277826,-76.704898,"This side of the road down to the creek is full of pawpaw trees. Most aren't fruiting, but I saw one with fruit relatively close to the road. I'm unsure of the status of this land, but I don't think it's private due to its location and proximity to the railroa","community","https://fallingfruit.org/locations/1827863","2023-05-27 02:46:35 UTC","","unknown",false,"Access unknown in Falling Fruit."],["1827864-116","pawpaw","337 Dunning St, Williamsburg, VA 23185, USA","Pawpaw","Asimina triloba",37.279073,-76.703024,"Small fruiting clump of trees. You have to go off of the path to reach these, but it's only maybe 20 yards from the path and through a grassy/cleared area. Unfortunately, pretty small yield this year (2023), maybe 3-4 fruits in May\u2014best left for the wildlife. ","community","https://fallingfruit.org/locations/1827864","2023-05-27 02:52:40 UTC","","unknown",false,"Access unknown in Falling Fruit."],["1822548-246","persimmon","240A Gooch Dr, Williamsburg, VA 23186, USA","American persimmon","Diospyros virginiana",37.270854,-76.71349,"Located near the stairs at the bend of the path around the Crim Dell. Tree is on the inside of the curve, opposite of the lamp post. Tree is too tall to pick fruit from its branches, but fallen fruit can be gathered on the edge of the path on the side closest ","community","https://fallingfruit.org/locations/1822548","2022-09-30 19:39:07 UTC","Public","open",true,"Falling Fruit access: Public."],["1825180-12","persimmon","301 N Boundary St, Williamsburg, VA 23185, USA","Persimmon","Diospyros",37.273612,-76.707417,"Persimmon tree with tons of fruit! Access: Private but overhanging. Falling Fruit season: October-November.","community","https://fallingfruit.org/locations/1825180","2023-03-09 21:08:10 UTC","Private but overhanging","private",false,"Falling Fruit access: Private but overhanging."],["1919620-291","serviceberry","301 Monticello Ave, Williamsburg, VA 23185, USA","Allegheny serviceberry","Amelanchier laevis",37.277711000000004,-76.7233545,"Access: Public.","community","https://fallingfruit.org/locations/1919620","2023-10-08 21:29:27 UTC","Public","open",true,"Falli